4. What is Jenkins architecture?

Jenkins follows a master-slave architecture. 
The Jenkins master is responsible for managing the overall Jenkins environment, including scheduling builds, dispatching builds to the slaves, and monitoring the slaves. 
The Jenkins slaves are responsible for executing the build tasks assigned by the master.
 This architecture allows for distributed builds and scalability, as multiple slaves can be added to handle more build tasks simultaneously.

