33. What is the difference between freestyle and pipeline jobs?

Freestyle jobs are a traditional type of Jenkins job that allows you to define build steps and post-build actions using a graphical user interface.
Pipeline jobs, on the other hand, are defined using code (Jenkinsfile) and provide more flexibility and control over the build process.
Table of differences:
| Aspect               | Freestyle Job                          | Pipeline Job                            |
|----------------------|----------------------------------------       |-----------------------------------------| 
| Definition           | Defined using a graphical user interface      | Defined using code (Jenkinsfile)         |
| Flexibility          | Limited flexibility in defining build steps   | More flexible, allows for complex build processes |
| Version Control      | Not easily versioned                          | Easily versioned as it is defined in a Jenkinsfile stored in source control |
| Parallel Execution   | Not natively supported, requires plugins      | Natively supports parallel execution of stages |
| Error Handling       | Limited error handling capabilities           | Provides better error handling and recovery options |   
| Reusability          | Limited reusability of build steps            | Allows for reusable code and shared libraries |
| Visualization        | Basic visualization of build steps            | Provides a more visual representation of the pipeline stages and their status |
| peer review          | Not easily peer-reviewed                      | Easily peer-reviewed as it is defined in code and can be stored in source control |

