57. How do you stop duplicate builds running at the same time?

To stop duplicate builds from running at the same time in Jenkins, you can use the "Throttle Concurrent Builds" plugin. This plugin allows you to limit the number of concurrent builds for a specific job or across the entire Jenkins environment. You can configure the plugin to allow only one build to run at a time for a particular job, which will prevent duplicate builds from running simultaneously. 
Additionally, you can also use the "Lockable Resources" plugin to create locks around specific resources (e.g., files, directories) that are used in the build process, ensuring that only one build can access those resources at a time and preventing duplicate builds from running concurrently.

